Trendkite, Inc. Key Developments

TrendKite Expands Executive Team to Support Product Development and Rapid Growth
Apr 20 16
TrendKite announced the hire of John De Oliveira, Russ Somers and Jennifer Cantu to support the company's rapid growth. TrendKite has seen 600% year-over-year sales growth, expanded its office space and quadrupled the size of its workforce since the start of 2015. De Oliveira joins TrendKite as vice president of product. In this role, he will drive innovative solutions for TrendKite's customers by bringing expertise in big data, natural language processing, machine learning and information products to the world of public relations technology. De Oliveira has more than 20 years of experience in managing products and technology. He has previously held product management leadership positions at Sprinklr, Dachis Group and Dun & Bradstreet. As vice president of marketing, Somers will bring TrendKite's continued innovation to market by leveraging 20 years of marketing experience ranging from high-growth startups to Fortune 500 companies. In addition to having led teams at Invodo, SonarDesign, Dun & Bradstreet, and Dell, Somers serves as an adviser to a number of Austin-based companies, including eyeQ and Edgecase.io. Cantu, vice president of people, has more than 18 years of experience recruiting and managing talent for corporate teams. She will manage recruitment and culture for TrendKite's fast-growing employee base. Prior to joining TrendKite, Cantu led talent and culture for nine years at Spiceworks, where she helped grow the team from a 30-person company to more than 500 employees.


